          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>כ"פ נוי ארק יום ויו על פ' מו"מ</add>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>Mr. <sic>Isaach</sic>
                                        <addressee>Leeser</addressee></p>
                              <p>Minister of the Congregation</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Mikveh Israel</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">Yiddish</hi>
                                        </add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <placeName>N. Y.</placeName>
                                        <date><hi rend="underline">Friday</hi>, Pericope
                                                  Matoh<add>?</add></date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <date>(June), 1849</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>Peace, etc, etc, to my friend <addressee>Rabbi
                                        Isaac</addressee>:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Yesterday I received your letter and do not
                                        delay<lb/> to reply to you in accordance with your wish.
                                        With<lb/> regard to the Torah, which I am writing at your
                                        order,<lb/> herewith call your attention to the fact that it
                                        is almost<lb/> half done. I am really diligent in this work,
                                        and if God<lb/> grant me health, I expect to finish it in
                                        five or six<lb/> weeks. I have been occupied with a variety
                                        of things I cann<add>?</add><lb/> mention here and
                                        celebrated the completion of the Torah, upon<lb/> which I
                                        was working when you were here, only last
                                                  <date>Shabu<lb/>oth</date>. I hope to God, and
                                        thank him, that everyone is well in<lb/> my family. That of
                                        course, is the most important matter<lb/> I hope the same is
                                        true in your case, and in the case of<lb/> those who are
                                        yours.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I have a proposition for you. <persName>Mr.
                                                  Kurschitt</persName> saw the<lb/> Torah which you
                                        had. I looked through it and found it<lb/> Kosher. I made
                                        new “Etz-claims”* for it and it is now con<lb/>siderably
                                        lighter. I have the authority to sell it. If you, a<lb/> any
                                        time, have need for it, you might turn to me. If not<lb/>
                                        have the kindness to recommend me in the “Occident”</p>
                              <p>1—as scribe, to write new Torahs, with respect to which I<lb/> show
                                        excellent recommendations, I have written
                                        seve<add>?</add><lb/> and the people have been very much
                                        satisfied with them<lb/> well as with my T'phillim and
                                                  Mezzot<add>?</add>.</p>
                              <p>2—that I have at hand two excellent Torahs, one big one<lb/> and
                                        one twenty inches long. Also all kinds of books,<lb/> prayer
                                        books for <date>Rosh Hashonah</date> printed in
                                                  <placeName>Furth</placeName>,
                                                  <placeName>Albach</placeName>,<lb/> and
                                                  <placeName>Vienna</placeName>. Also prayer books,
                                        pentateuchs of all<lb/> kinds, German and Polish ritual.
                                        Also very good woolen<lb/> and silk Talithum.</p>
                              <p>*rollers.</p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>That how you might present this in the shortest and<lb/> best way.
                                        I need not tell you. Since you <del>see what<lb/> I have
                                                  through my</del> yourself are convinced of my<lb/>
                                        ability as a scribe you will know how to recommend<lb/> one.
                                        Whatever expense this will involve, I will gladly<lb/> pay.
                                        With best wishes,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">Sincerely yours,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Notta</persName>, son of
                                                  <persName>Isaac Dov</persName></p>
                              <p>Scribe</p>
                              <p>N.B.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I want to let you know something new.
                                                  <persName>Mr.<lb/> Frank</persName>, a printer, is
                                        having prayer books printed<lb/> with an English translation
                                        just like your<lb/> prayer books in Octavo. This obviously
                                        will decre<add>?</add><lb/> your sale. He set the price of
                                        $1. each, which will <add>?</add><lb/> our sales a bit weak.
                                        This I let you know, not as a<lb/> matter of gossip, God
                                        forbid. However, I beg of you<lb/> not to reveal who told
                                        you.</p>
                    </body>
